review_blob: 33 cl bottle at Bishops Arms, Karlstad. Pours a clear golden color with a small white head. Aroma is fruity with notes of citrus, orange and peach. Flavour is fruity with notes of orange and a marked bitterness. Light to medium bodied with soft carbonation. A decent start for this new brewery!

Pours a slightly hazy golden color with a two finger head. Aroma of lemon, green apples, gooseberries, and funk. Flavour is sour and dry with a touch of lemon, unripe fruits, gooseberries and the usual funk. Light to mediumbodied with lively, refreshing carbonation. A lovely Gueuze!
Golden color. Fruity, lightly spicy aroma with notes of citrus. Flavour is lightly sweet and fruity. Medium bodied with lively carbonation. Good one!

Golden color with a big white head. Spicy, fruity aroma with a touch of citrus. Dry, yet refreshing and fruity flavour with a some funk. Light to medium bodied with lively carbonation. A great saison.
beer_name: Boulevard Smokestack Series - Tank 7 Farmhouse Ale

review_blob: Dark brown color with a nice white head. Aroma is fruity with notes of plums, caramel, candy. Well balanced sweet taste, with notes of dark fruits. Medium to fullbodied with rather lively carbonation. A world class beer, indeed.
Golden color with a nice white head. Funky bretty aroma with hints of lemon. Flavour is dry and lightly acidic. Lively and refreshing carbonation. Very nice.
Pours a darked red color with a small white head. Funk, berries, oak in the aroma. Lovely sour and funky flavour with notes of currants. Lively carbonation. A good sour.

Bottle from the brewer. Slightly hazy pale golden color. Aroma of caramel and sweet honey. Flavour is slightly sweet with notes of caramel, honey and just a tiny bit of smoke (you can feel that the whisky malt is there, but its very subtle). Light to mediumbodied, soft carbonation.

Dark brown, almost black color with a beige head. Fresh passionfruit and citrus in the aroma. Flavour is just lightly roasted and dominated by tropical fruity hops and lingering bitterness. Mediumbodied with a good lively carbonation. Very, very tasty black IPA.

Bottle at Bishops Arms, Karlstad. Pours a red-brown color with a very small head. Aroma of caramel, toffee and fudge with some very slight dried fruit notes.. also some alcohol, of course, since this is a young bottle. Flavour is dominated by caramely- and toffee like malt, and warming alcohol. Fullbodied with flat carbonation. This is tasty, but needs some aging. But very good for being this young and strong.

On tap at Bishops Arms, Karlstad. Pours a slightly hazy orange color with large white head, som lacing. Aroma of grapefruit, citrus, orange and some slight caramel. Flavour is fruity and hoppy with citrus, grapefruit, mandarines and orange whith a light caramely malt base. Balanced bitterness in the finish. Mediumbodied with lively carbonation. A very refreshing and tasty IPA!

Pours an almost black color with a small pale-brown head. Aroma is lightly roasted with cocoa, coffee, fudge and candy. Flavour is sweet and candy like with lightly roasted notes of chocolate and fudge. Fullbodied with soft carbonation - very smooth. Nice stuff.
beer_name: De Molen Tsarina Esra Imperial Porter

review_blob: Pours a brown color with a mediumsized white head. Aroma of caramel, spices, banana and dried fruits. Flavour is sweet with caramel and dried fruits, with some light phenolic notes in the background of spices and banana. Medium to fullbodied with lively carbonation. Nice stuff this!

Pours a hazy orange color with a mediumsized white head. Arom of clove, ornage peels and citrus. Flavour is lightly acidic with notes of citrus, orange peel and clove. Medium bodied with lively carbonation. A nice wit.

Black color with a mediumsized beige head. Roasted aroma with cocoa powder, coffee, and some phenolic clove like notes, alsom some herbs. Flavour is dry and roasted with cocoa, coffee and liquorice, and also some phenolic notes. Medium bitterness with some herb-like/grassy notes in the finish. Mediumbodied with rather lively carbonation. Hm, not that convinced.

Pours a black color with a small brown head - not much lacing. Aroma of coffee, chocolate, dried fruits, liquorice and whiskey. Flavour is rather vinous with dired fruits, coffee, chocolate, liquorice and whiskey. Rather warming alcohol. Not so sweet. Fullbodied with soft carbonation. A good beer.

Pours a black color with a mediumsized beige-brown head. Aroma is roasted and burned with notes of coffee, liquorice, chocolate, charcoal, tar , some grassy hops and noticable alcohol. Flavour is burned with charcoal, tar, coffee and dark chocolate. Theres also some grassy hops and rather harsh, unbalanced bitterness. Some alcohol, which gets a bit too much for me, is notacible in the finish. Fullbodied  with soft carbonation. Not my cup of imperial stout to be totally honest.

Pours a darkbrown color with a mediumsized beige head. Aroma of coffee, dark chocolate, smoke and some dried fruits. Flavour of coffee, dark chocolate and light smoke, and a bit salty finish. Medium bodied with soft carbonation. Rather tasty beer!

Bottle. Pours a dark red-brown color with mediumsized beige head. Aroma is fruity with notes of currants, raisins, caramel, dark bread and flowers. Flavour is fruity with notes of currants, light caramel, flowers, dark bread and earth. Slightly dry with a low to medium bitterness. Light bodied with soft carbonation - quite thin. OK beer.

Slightly hazy orange color with a large beige-white head, some lacing. Aroma is nd fruity with berries, flowers and caramel. Flavour of flowers, fruit, berries, caramel. Rather sweet with a balanced bitterness. Mediumbodied with soft carbonation. Nice.
beer_name: BrewDog IPA Is Dead - Bramling X

review_blob: Pours a redbrown color with a mediumsized, creamy beige-white head. Aroma of pine needles, grapefruit, citrus, nuts and caramel. Flavour of grapefruit, resin, pine needles, citrus, nuts and a malty toffee background. Mediumbodied with average carbonation.

Pours a red copper color with a white medium sized head. Aroma of smoke (not as much smoked sausage as in the normal Schlenkerla, but more wood and tar) and malty toffee/caramel notes. Flavour is smoky with notes of caramel and dried fruits. Light bitter finish. Mediumbodied with average carbonation. Great.

Slightly hazy with a small white head. Aroma is funky with green apples,gooseberries, lemon and barnyard. Flavour is tart and dry with mostly  green apples and gooseberries together with some light wood, barnyard and cheese. Light bodied with lively carbonation. Nice stuff!

Bottle. Pours a hazy golden-yellow with a large white head, some lacing. Phenolic, spicy aroma with notes of bubble gum, citrus, orange, banana and grass. Flavour is dry and fruity with spices (like clove) and some refreshing citrusy notes, banana and grass. Bitter finish. Light to mediumbodied with lively carbonation. Very tasty.
UPDATED: DEC 30, 2012
beer_name: Great Divide Yeti Imperial Stout - Chocolate Oak Aged

review_blob: Pours a red copper color with a small beige head. Aroma of caramel, citrusy hops, oak and vanilla. Flavour is quite sweet with toffee/caramel, citrus, pine, wood and vanilla. Quite grassy bitterness. Medium bodied. A bit unbalanced and weird, but too bad.
beer_name: Great Divide Anniversary Wood Aged Double IPA

review_blob: Pours a slighty hazy lightbrown/amber color with a mediumsized head, not much lacing. Aroma of toffee/caramel, almonds, nuts, resin, grapefruit and fruity esters. Flavour is quite sweet with notes of toffee/caramel, nuts and bitter finish of grapefruit, pine and resin. Fullbodied with average carbonation, pretty smooth. Nice.

Bottle as "Hststout". Black color, medium sized brown head, some lacing. Aroma of coffee, roasted malt, milk chocolate, light smoke, and liquorice. Flavour is slightly burned, theres notes of coffee and milk chocolate. Sligthly sweet, which dissapears behind the almost acidic coffee notes. Light bitter finish. Mediumbodied, soft carbonation, smooth mouthfeel. Rather tasty stout!

Pours an almost black color with a small beige head. Aroma of chocolate, liqourice, some coffee and dried fruits - a bit vinous. Flavour of coffee, liqourice and dried fruits (raisins, plums). Rather vinous feel to it, just slightly sweet. Mediumbodied with soft carbonation. Tasty! Rather "aged" feeling.

Bottle. Sligthly hazy yellow-orange color with a medium sized head - not much lacing. Aroma of citrus, grapefruit, cookies, orange zest and apricot. Flavour of cookies, grapefruit, citrus and apricot. Mediumbodied, average carbonation. Dont know how fresh this was, but its an average IPA - nothing special.

Bottle. Pours a copper color with a nice white head, some lacing. Aroma of citrus, cloudberries, gooseberries, and some black currants. Flavour is citrus hoppy with notes of currant leaves, gooseberries and cloudberries with a touch of toffee/caramel. Medium to fullbodied with rather soft carbonation. A tasty beer!
beer_name: BrewDog Hello, My Name is Ingrid

review_blob: Hazy yellow with a small white head which dissapears after a while. Aroma is lightly spicy and fruity with notes of citrus. Flavour is your typical Wit with a citrus-like tartness and some spices. Light bodied with average to lively carbonation. Not so special, but pretty decent.

Pours a golden color with a white head. Aroma of orange, citrus, grapefruit and maybe som cookies. Flavour is hoppy with citrus, tropical fruits, cookie-like malt, and a refreshing grapefruity bitterness. Light to medium bodied with a rather lively carbonation. A tasty APA!

Pours a copper color with a beige-white head. Aroma of bread, caramel, dried fruit and some alcohol. Flavour is rather sweet with caramel, bread, sugar, dried fruit and some warming alcohol. Rather smooth wit soft carbonation. Medium bodied.

Hazy orange color with a compact white head which slowly fades away and leaves some lacing on the glass.

Aroma of exotic fruits like mango, pineapple, starfruit, peach, passion fruit, tangerine, and grapefruit. Behind the hops theres some bready malt with a touch of caramel.

Flavour of mango, pineapple and passion fruit which leads to strong grapefruity bitterness which is lightly balanced buy the cookie-like malt and caramel. Pine needles and resin can also be found.

Fullbodied with soft to average carbonation. Damn nice!
Clear golden color, small white head. Worty, sweet flavour. Light bitterness. Not much to say about this...
Pours a copper color with a mediumsized white head. Aroma of nuts, toffee, grass. Flavour of caramel, grass, some grapefruit and a rather harsh bitterness. Light to mediumbodied. OK.

Pours an almost black color with a mediumsized beige head. Roasted, slightly burned and vinous aroma; notes of nuts, dark chocolate, coffee, and dried fruits. Flavour is mostly roasted and burned with dark chocolate, dried fruits (raisins, plums) and nuts. Also some earthy coffee and vanilla. Finishes bitter. Medium bodied with soft carbonation. Really nice.

Red brown, rather clear color with a large beige-white head which leaves some lacing. Aroma of toffee, almonds, dried fruits and light spices. Flavour is lightly sweet with toffee and burned almonds, dried fruits, and some light warming alcohol. Also some candy-like notes and a light bitterness in the finish. Mediumbodied with soft carbonation and a smooth texture. Nice.

Red brown with a large beigewhite head, some lacing. Aroma of caramel, dried fruits, spices, brown sugar, and alcohol. Flavour of caramelized sugar, phenolic spicy notes and dried fruits/raisins. Also some earthy, grassy notes with a bitter finish. Rather dry. Fullbodied with average to lively carbonation. Rather nice.

Pours a black color with a large, creamy beige head - some lacing. Aroma of coffee, dark chocolate, liquorice and toffee. Flavour is mostly roasted with coffee, some light spicy notes, and dark chocolate. Ligthly sweet with hints of toffee and a balanced bitterness. Average carbonation. Fullbodied. A nice and interesting imperial stout - a bit different.

Deep red color with a mediumsized pink head. Aroma of raspberries, both fruity and more candy-like raspberries. Flavour is tart, but yet very simple and a bit sweet with raspberries (not that funky). Lightbodied with average carbonation. Not bad, but not that special either.

Hazy yellow color, small white head. Aroma is lightly acidic with a touch of lemon/citrus, spices, orange, yeast and almost some soap. Flavour is lightly tart and dry with citrus, orange and some light spices. Light bitter finish. Light bodied with lively carbonation. A fresh and tasty wit!

Sligthly hazy orange color, large beige head, some lacing. Aroma of pine needles, resin, orange and some perfume, some weak coffee. Flavour of pine needles and grapefrui, some faint coffee notes, and a touch of caramel. Long, rather strong bitterness. Mediumbodied with soft carbonation. Not that convinced.
beer_name: Mikkeller Koppi Tomahawk x Odoo Shakiso Coffee IPA

review_blob: Red brown color with mediumsized white head. Malty, bready aroma with some caramel. Also some grain and minerals. Flavour is malt focused with some crispbread, caramel, some fruity esters and light mineral-like note. Light bitterness in the finish. Light to medium bodied, the carbonation is soft. Decent beer.

Hazy orange color with a large white head, lots of lacing on the glass. Aroma of citrus, grapefruit, pine needles and resin. Also some cookies and caramel in the background. Flavour is dry with notes of grapefruit and citrus together with apricot. A caramely maltiness makes it through before it finishes with a marked bitterness. Very nice beer.

Red color, beige-white head. Aroma of toffee, caramel, pine needles and grapefruit. Flavour is pretty balanced between the malty, lightly sweet caramel and the grapefruity/piny hops. Marked bitterness. Light to mediumbodied. OK beer.

Pours a golden color with a nice white head, some lacing. Aroma of grapefruit, pine needles and apricot. Flavour is hoppy with refreshing piny/grapefruity hops and marked bitterness. Carbonation is lively. Light to medium bodied. Very nice.

Pours a clear golden color with a medium sized head. Aroma of resin, pine needles, grapefruit, apricot and cookies. Flavour of pine needles, grapefruit and a large, almost sharpe bitterness. Also some apricot, orange and caramel. Average to lively carbonation. Mediumbodied.

Pours a black colour with a small brown head. Aroma of roasted coffee, dark chocolate, vanilla, oak and bourbon. Flavour is roasted with coffee, chocolate, vanilla and bourbon, with a toch of almonds. Very smooth mouthfeel, the carbonation is soft. Fullbodied.
